# **Royal Wood Skip**

The&nbsp;**Royal Wood Skip**&nbsp;is a&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;[Dark Souls](/darksouls)&nbsp;that allows the player to skip a large portion of the&nbsp;[Royal Wood](https://darksouls.wikidot.com/royal-wood)&nbsp;by abusing the&nbsp;[Fall Damage Cancel&nbsp;or&nbsp;Fall Control Quitout](/ds1remaster/fall-damages-cancel)&nbsp;mechanics. The skip saves about 40s or 30s IGT for each method respectively. It was discovered by Distortion2 in February 2015 on PTDE version of the game.

The most common way to perform this skip is by using memerolls because it is faster and easier than any other methods.

You can not perform this skip in [Glitchless categories](/ds1remaster/glitchless) of the game.

## External Resources

- Memeroll setup: [https://www.twitch.tv/videos/1221776096?t=0h37m28s](https://www.twitch.tv/videos/1221776096?t=0h37m28s) by catalystz on YouTube.
- Others setups ( not recommended ) [https://youtu.be/UTkffjeJGLs](https://youtu.be/UTkffjeJGLs) by catalystz on YouTube.
